Pre-Game Insights: Georgia and Czech Republic are aiming for promotion from League B Group 1 in the 2024-25 UEFA Nations League.
Georgia has a strong home record, having lost only one of their last 13 matches in front of their fans since November 2021.
Czech Republic was eliminated in the group stage of Euro 2024, finishing rock bottom with only one point.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is the opening fixture for both nations in the 2024-25 Nations League campaign.
Georgia and Czech Republic have a history of close encounters, with Georgia winning their previous encounter at Euro 2024.
Others: Georgia's team features notable players like Giorgi Mamardashvili and Khvicha Kvaratskhelia.
Czech Republic's squad includes Patrik Schick and Matej Kovar.
